President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Danny Lam Nguyen and John C. Truong as Associate Judges on the Superior Court of the District of Columbia. Danny Lam Nguyen currently works as a Trial Attorney in the Criminal Division of the United States Department of Justice, where he focuses on prosecuting complex financial fraud crimes. He has previously served as an Assistant United States Attorney, prosecuting cases involving domestic violence and sexual abuse. Nguyen has also worked in private practice at Wilmer Cutler Pickering Hale and Dorr, LLP, and served as a law clerk to Judge Reggie B. Walton of the United States District Court. He holds a B.A. and M.Ed. from the University of California, Los Angeles, and a J.D. from Georgetown University Law Center, magna cum laude.

John C. Truong, on the other hand, currently serves as Senior Litigation Counsel in the Civil Division of the United States Attorney's Office for the District of Columbia. His work involves prosecuting cases related to fraud and other misconduct to recover lost money. Truong has previously represented Federal officials and executive government agencies in civil litigation and has experience prosecuting criminal offenses. Before joining the United States Attorney's Office, he worked in private practice at Morgan, Lewis & Bockius, LLP. Truong also serves as an Adjunct Professor at the George Washington University Law School. He holds a B.A. from the University of Southern California, an M.A. from the American University, and a J.D. from the American University, Washington College of Law.